A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a stern office worker in a cardigan systematically removing wilted, ghostly translucent figures from an enormous wooden card catalog filing system, each drawer overflowing with index cards. The ghostly figures float upward and dissolve into wisps of smoke. The scene is rendered in muted olive greens, warm browns, and sepia tones with halftone dot patterns typical of mid-century print advertisements. The filing cabinet stretches impossibly tall into the background, creating a sense of overwhelming organizational scale. Dramatic desk lamp lighting casts long shadows across scattered index cards on a wooden desk.
